source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_SEQ_00<tab>Urianger is trying to make sense of the strange phenomenon afflicting the residents of Gatetown.

TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_SEQ_01<tab>By all indications, the residents of Gatetown are under Vauthry's mind control, and as Urianger attempts to fathom its workings, Alisaie arrives with your old friend Kai-Shirr in tow. Based on his account of events, it would seem that those who have lived in Gatetown the longest were the first to be affected. All the pieces fall into place when Y'shtola subsequently returns brandishing a loaf of meol. With dread and disbelief, Ryne immediately recognizes the Eulmoran staple for what it is: sin eater flesh, the consumption of which apparently renders one susceptible to Vauthry's influence. This sickening revelation leaves everyone aghast, but the horrors do not end there... Recalling the words you heard during your first visit to Eulmore, Alphinaud shares his suspicion that citizens who have outlived their usefulness are being deliberately turned into sin eaters. Suppressing the urge to gag, you endeavor to put such thoughts from your mind, and concentrate instead on the task at hand: hunting down the Lightwarden. The being is all but certain to be hiding in Eulmore's upper levels, and it is decided that you will lead the charge into the city.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_SEQ_01<tab>Vous avez fini par comprendre ce qui se tramait au Vestibule, en mettant au jour une effroyable vérité<var 1D /var>: le méol, denrée distribuée gratuitement aux locaux, serait en réalité de la viande de purgateur<var 1D /var>! Consommée durant des années, elle aurait peu à peu transformé les habitants, les rendant vulnérables au contrôle mental de don Vauthry. Indignés par une telle pratique, Alisaie et Alphinaud ont résolu d'en finir au plus vite. Parlez à ce dernier, au Vestibule, pour partir à l'assaut d'Eulmore.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_SEQ_02<tab>Together with your comrades, you sally forth into Eulmore.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_SEQ_02<tab>Vous vous êtes frayé un chemin à travers des hordes de citoyens esclaves de don Vauthry, jusqu'à la place de l'éthérite où vous attendait Ran'jit. L'inflexible général vous a alors provoqué<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var> en duel, et vous n'avez eu d'autre choix que de lui passer sur le corps.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_SEQ_03<tab>While the others keep Vauthry's thralls at bay, you press on to the Canopy, where you are confronted by a lone Ran'jit. Driven by a resolve all his own, the old soldier brings the sum of his might to bear against you, but you narrowly emerge the victor, striking him down once and for all. Rejoined by your comrades, you then ascend to the Emergent and find Vauthry having dinner in his chamber. There, Ryne finally realizes that <var 1A 02 /var>he<var 1A 01 /var> is the Lightwarden, being an unholy mixture of man and sin eater. Before you are able to act, however, Vauthry sprouts wings and takes to the skies. Rushing to the balcony, you are met with an impossible sight: the peak of Mt. Gulg, torn from the earth and floating in the heavens. It is there that Vauthry appears to have fled. With your quarry out of reach, you decide to suspend the hunt, that you might instead render aid to the casualties of the battle.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_SEQ_03<tab>Dans les quartiers du gouverneur, vous avez découvert avec stupeur que le grand purgateur d'Eulmore et don Vauthry ne faisaient qu'un<var 1D /var>! Après une vive altercation, votre adversaire s'est soudain doté d'une paire d'ailes, puis il vous a faussé compagnie à la faveur d'un hurlement strident. Par le balcon, vous avez constaté qu'il s'était réfugié sur le Mont Gulg, le plus haut pic de Kholusia... qui s'est mys<var 16 /var>té<var 16 /var>rieu<var 16 /var>se<var 16 /var>ment mis à flotter dans les airs<var 1D /var>! Alphinaud vous a alors demandé d'abandonner votre poursuite, souhaitant dans un premier temps soigner les Eulmoriens blessés. Parlez à Thancred, à la place de l'Éthérite d'Eulmore.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_SEQ_04<tab>To your relief, Thancred informs you that Ryne is able to counteract the effects of Vauthry's mind control, and is busy tending to the afflicted one by one. There are, however, countless wounded requiring attention, and you are asked to assist in the relief effort.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_SEQ_04<tab>Ryne s'est révélée capable de désenvoûter les victimes de Vauthry. Joignez vos forces à celles de vos amis pour aider la population d'Eulmore à se relever de cette rude épreuve.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_000<tab>The gears are clearly turning in Urianger's mind. Why don't you ask him what he makes of all this?
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_000<tab>Je ne sais pas ce qu'en pense Urianger, mais tout ça ne présage rien de bon à mes yeux...
TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RESIDENT03630_000_005<tab>Qu-qu'est-ce qu'ils ont tous<var 1D /var>!? Ils me font peur<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALISAIE_000_010<tab>I'm fine, <var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var>. Shaking with fury, but fine. Let's go.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALISAIE_000_010<tab>Ça ira, même si je ne te cacherai pas que j'ai les nerfs en pelote... Un tel mépris pour la vie humaine, ça me révulse.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_015<tab>We are like to encounter Ran'jit again. One can only hope he's still licking his wounds.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_015<tab>Si toute l'armée eulmorienne a été mobilisée, Ran'jit est forcément là. J'espère que notre combat l'aura au moins affaibli...

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_016<tab>Yet even without him, Eulmore is an eminently defensible city─as you doubtless gleaned during your visit.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_016<tab>De toute façon, nous aurons fort à faire. Cette cité est conçue pour être dif<var 16 /var>fi<var 16 /var>ci<var 16 /var>le<var 16 /var>ment prenable. D'ailleurs, je lui trouve des airs de Limsa Lominsa du premier reflet.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_017<tab>When last I set foot inside its walls, I almost mistook it for dear old Limsa─but it is <var 1A 02 /var>full<var 1A 01 /var> of unpleasant surprises. All of which is a long way of saying: be on your guard.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_017<tab>Bon, il y a peut-être un peu moins de coupe-jarrets ici... mais ce n'est pas une raison pour baisser notre garde.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RYNE_000_020<tab>The uppermost level of the city houses Vauthry's chambers. He must keep the Warden close.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RYNE_000_020<tab>Le sommet d'Eulmore, aussi appelé La Cime... Les quartiers de Vauthry sont là-bas. Il pourrait bien y avoir caché le grand purgateur...

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_URIANGER_000_025<tab>My heart is gripped by an unshakable sense of foreboding. Let us proceed with all care.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_URIANGER_000_025<tab>J'ai un mauvais pres<var 16 /var>sen<var 16 /var>ti<var 16 /var>ment... Tâchons de ne pas confondre vitesse et pré<var 16 /var>ci<var 16 /var>pi<var 16 /var>ta<var 16 /var>tion.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_YSHTOLA_000_030<tab>That Vauthry should so brazenly exert his influence over the people bespeaks his desperation. He will not go quietly.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_YSHTOLA_000_030<tab>Si Vauthry a lavé le cerveau de ses sujets, ce n'est sans doute pas pour rien. Le chemin jusqu'à lui s'annonce périlleux...

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_KAISHIRR_000_035<tab>Meol...is sin eater? Wicked white, we all scoffed the stuff without a second thought...
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_KAISHIRR_000_035<tab>Le méol, de la viande de purgateur<var 1D /var>?<var 1D /var>... Je crrrois que je vais vomir... Ça fait des années que tout le monde en mange sans se poser de questions...

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_KAISHIRR_000_036<tab>I never got near as much as the others, but...ugh...
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_KAISHIRR_000_036<tab>Heu<var 16 /var>reu<var 16 /var>se<var 16 /var>ment, je n'en ai jamais reçu que de toutes petites quantités. Je vis surrrtout de la cueillette et de la pêche.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_KAISHIRR_000_037<tab>Heh... The bitter greens and bony fish I got by on don't seem so bad no more...
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_KAISHIRR_000_037<tab>On peut dirrre que je l'ai échappé belle...

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_000_040<tab>When we step through the gates, we shall find not the place of hedonistic pleasure we remember, but a battlefield.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_000_040<tab>Mieux vaut que Kai-Shirr reste ici. Ce n'est plus un havre de paix et de volupté qui nous attend là-bas, mais un champ de bataille ô combien dangereux.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_000_041<tab>If you are prepared for this, then let us sally forth!
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_000_041<tab>Je vous le demande, <var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var>... Êtes-vous prêt<var 08 E905 ((e)) (()) /var> à passer à l'attaque<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_051<tab>The citizens appear to have calmed down for the moment. I can only assume Vauthry is otherwise engaged. Let's get to the upper level while we can.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_051<tab>On a réussi à repousser nos poursuivants, mais ils ne vont pas tarder à revenir à la charge. Dépêchons-nous d'atteindre le sommet<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_000_060<tab>My thanks again, <var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var>. We will seek out the wounded and render what aid we can.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_000_060<tab>Merci encore pour ce moment de répit. Je vais en profiter pour soigner un maximum de blessés.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALISAIE_000_065<tab>Some managed to shake off the mind control only to be caught in the chaos. We'll make sure they receive treatment as well.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALISAIE_000_065<tab>Certains Eulmoriens qui n'étaient pas sous l'emprise de Vauthry ont été blessés dans le feu de l'action. Eux aussi auront besoin de notre attention.
TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RYNE_000_070<tab>Tout va bien. Vous êtes en sécurité à présent.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_URIANGER_000_080<tab>Bereft of leadership, the soldiers have lost the will to fight. They pose no threat to us.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_URIANGER_000_080<tab>L'annonce de la mort du général Ran'jit a com<var 16 /var>plè<var 16 /var>te<var 16 /var>ment démotivé les troupes eulmoriennes. Nous n'avons plus rien à craindre d'elles a priori.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_YSHTOLA_000_085<tab>So this was how the citizens lived─the Eulmoran dream. They are in for quite a rude awakening.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_YSHTOLA_000_085<tab>J'imagine sans mal le train de vie que devaient mener tous ces gens. Pour eux, le retour à la réalité s'annonce brutal...

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_090<tab>Good news, <var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var>. It would seem that Ryne is indeed able to reverse the effects of Vauthry's influence.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_090<tab>Bonne nouvelle, <var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var>. Ryne est ef<var 16 /var>fec<var 16 /var>ti<var 16 /var>ve<var 16 /var>ment capable de rompre le charme de Vauthry.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_091<tab>Even as we speak, she tends to the afflicted in turn. The problem being: there's no end to them.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_091<tab>En revanche, on manque de mains avec tous ces blessés...

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_092<tab>We're trying to provide what relief we can to those who are waiting, and would appreciate your help, if you're willing.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_000_092<tab>Vous voulez bien nous aider à remettre de l'ordre dans cette cité<var 1D /var>? Ne serait-ce que pour faire plaisir à Alphinaud...

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_SYSTEM_000_093<tab>You can now attune with the aetheryte in Eulmore!
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_SYSTEM_000_093<tab>Vous pouvez désormais vous harmoniser avec l'éthérite d'Eulmore.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_010<tab>Do no more than is necessary to subdue the civilians!
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_010<tab>Nous devons épargner la vie des civils. Contentez-vous de les neutraliser.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_BATTLETALK_000_020<tab>We're wasting time. Ryne─we hold them here while the others press on!
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_THANCRED_BATTLETALK_000_020<tab>Les amis... Dès que vous voyez une ouverture, foncez. Ryne et moi, on reste ici.
TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RYNE_BATTLETALK_000_030<tab>Nous allons faire de notre mieux pour les retenir<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_031<tab>Have care, you two! The rest of you, with me!
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_031<tab>C'est le moment<var 1D /var>! Venez, on y va<var 1D /var>!
TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RYNE_BATTLETALK_000_032<tab>N-non... Je n'ai pas été à la hauteur...

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_040<tab>Their minds are not their own, remember! Avoid harming them wherever possible!
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_040<tab>Des soldats, eux aussi envoûtés... Vous savez quoi faire<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_YSHTOLA_BATTLETALK_000_050<tab>There is no end to them... Urianger─would you care to make a stand?
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_YSHTOLA_BATTLETALK_000_050<tab>On y sera encore demain à ce rythme... Urianger, tu m'aides à faire barrage<var 1D /var>?

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_URIANGER_BATTLETALK_000_060<tab>Gladly. <var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var>─pray press on with the others when the opportunity doth arise.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_URIANGER_BATTLETALK_000_060<tab>Compris. Pressez le pas dès que ça se calmera.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALISAIE_BATTLETALK_000_061<tab>The way's clear! Come on, you two!
TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_070<tab>Confound it! More of them! And we were almost through!
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_070<tab>Oh non, pas encore... Heu<var 16 /var>reu<var 16 /var>se<var 16 /var>ment, il ne reste que cette porte à franchir<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALISAIE_BATTLETALK_000_080<tab>Right, my turn to make a heroic stand! As soon as there's a lull, push on!
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALISAIE_BATTLETALK_000_080<tab>Je vous laisse continuer... Courez dès que vous aurez le champ libre<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_081<tab>Now, <var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var>─into the tower! Just you take care, Alisaie!
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_081<tab><var 2C ((<var 29 EB02 /var>)) (( )) 02 /var>, c'est maintenant ou jamais. Franchissons la porte<var 1D /var>! Fais attention à toi, Alisaie<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_CLOWNOFRED_BATTLETALK_000_100<tab>Apologies, friends...but you've reached a dead end. And on <var 1A 02 /var>this<var 1A 01 /var> sorry track, there's no turning back.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_CLOWNOFRED_BATTLETALK_000_100<tab>Désolée, mais votre course folle s'achève ici<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_CLOWNOFBLUE_BATTLETALK_000_110<tab>We've a good life here, see, and we're not about to lose it. But fair's fair─we'll give you a good death.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_CLOWNOFBLUE_BATTLETALK_000_110<tab>Vous voulez ruiner notre petit paradis<var 1D /var>? Allons, faites-nous plutôt le plaisir de mourir<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_111<tab>If you would fight us of your own volition, then we will not hold back!
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_111<tab>Vous voulez vraiment vous battre, hein<var 1D /var>? Vous l'aurez voulu<var 1D /var>!
TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_CLOWNOFRED_BATTLETALK_000_120<tab>Nous allons vous offrir une mort... cocasse<var 1D /var>!
TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_CLOWNOFBLUE_BATTLETALK_000_130<tab>Oh oui, rions pour l'éternité<var 1D /var>! Il nous suffit de tous y passer<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_140<tab>Let us climb to the Canopy. From there we will take the Crown Lift.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_140<tab>Continuons de grimper jusqu'à La Voûte. On prendra le Liber à partir de là.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_160<tab>Still more soldiers... Leave them to me and press on!
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_ALPHINAUD_BATTLETALK_000_160<tab>Voilà d'autres soldats... Laissez-les-moi, et continuez de grimper<var 1D /var>!

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RANJIT_BATTLETALK_000_170<tab>Ever since I submitted to my master's authority, I have been naught but a weapon.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RANJIT_BATTLETALK_000_170<tab>Je suis une arme au service de mon maître.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RANJIT_BATTLETALK_000_180<tab>I exist only to destroy. And destroy you I will.
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RANJIT_BATTLETALK_000_180<tab>Détruire, tuer, anéantir, telle est ma raison d'être... Vous ne m'échapperez pas.

source: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RANJIT_BATTLETALK_000_190<tab>It is time we settled this, villain.
TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RANJIT_BATTLETALK_000_191<tab>If you would pass me, you must endure all that I have learned on the battlefield... For I am a weapon forged in the fires of war!
target: TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RANJIT_BATTLETALK_000_191<tab>Venez tâter le résultat d'une vie de combats acharnés<var 1D /var>!
TEXT_LUCKME102_03631_RANJIT_BATTLETALK_000_200<tab>Argh... Ah... Je vous vois... mes chères petites filles...
